// monumentos i love Valledupar The strategy Yo Amo a Valledupar, leads the vallenatos to internalize in their hearts the sense of belonging to a city, beautiful, welcoming, cultural and musical; But it is not to love Valledupar, it is to demonstrate it, with a citizen culture, with care and cleanliness, speaking well of it and its people. With true love for this land full of charm, that we want to see in peace.r The poporos The Colosseum is one of the few that has a movable roof. Built in the late 90s, it is located in front of the sculpture of Los Poporos. This sculpture pays tribute to the three indigenous ethnic groups that still inhabit the Sierra Nevada, such as the Arhuacos, the Koguis and the Arzarios. Holy Ecce Homo El Santo Ecce Homo es el patrono de Valledupar. Una réplica de 30 metros, que vigila la ciudad desde el Cerro de las Antenas, es lugar de peregrinaje para devotos y meta para deportistas. Fue diseñada por el maestro colombiano Héctor Lombana, la estructura mide 35 metros de altura. Cacique Upar To the south east of the city stands the imposing El Cacique Upar, a beautiful sculpture representative of our indigenous aborigines who defended this region from the Spanish invaders. Curiously, it owes the name of our city, because Valledupar is an acronym for: Valle del Cacique Upar. He was the maximum chief of the Chimilas, a tribe of the region and those who had to move to the Sierra Nevada to avoid their total exterminationr
//sitios insignes Plaza Alfonso Lopez It is the founding square of the city. Venue of the famous Tarima Francisco el hombre and cradle of the Vallenata Legend Festival, which was held there for several decades until it was insufficient to accommodate the tourists who visited us. By touring the houses that surround it, you can learn about the history of the city, reading the plaques on each one of them. Its earthenware, from above, represent the paths of life of the Arhuaca cosmogony. It is currently being remodeled by the municipal mayor office. School Loperena it was created as a tribute to the memory of the vallenata heroine Doña María Concepción Loperena de Fernández de Castro, who rendered invaluable services to the independence of the Republic. Recognized as the Alma mater del Cesar for having trained most of the Departments leaders in the 20th century in their classrooms. In 1993, the facilities of the Colegio Nacional Loperena were declared National Monument of Colombia. A special permit is required to enter from 8:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. 1st of May square It is a park where you can enjoy, have fun and play. It is an attraction for children and adults alike. Concerts are held here since it has a wide platform and a large space. In addition, there is the monument of the guitars. This was installed on February 8, 2009 and is a tribute to the neighborhood festivities that start just the day after the Vallenato festival ends. Public space. Cesar Governorate The plaza has a flag park that has 27 27-meter-high poles on which the flags of each of the municipalities of the department of Cesar and Colombia fly. This recently renovated square is a green space for recreation that has several monuments that represent the idiosyncrasy of the region.Public space. Province park Place where Carlos Vives is honored as ambassador of our culture and folklore, who is also the godfather of this beautiful place. It will be located where the Ice Cream Park is today. It will be connected to the Juglares roundabout and will have water sources. The DC6 plane, parked there for the enjoyment of children, will become a museum of the life and work of this great artist.Public space. Vallenata legend park t is an architectural complex with an extension of 23 hectares, located north of the city of Valledupar, on the right bank of the Guatapurí river. Since 2004 the Vallenato Festival has been held here. It is an ecological, cultural, tourist and recreational site surrounded by bushes where the Compae Chipuco platform of the Cacique Upar Coliseum is located, with a capacity for 40,000 spectators. It is perhaps the best concert venue in the country.Free admission to all public from 8:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. Novalito Park Leisure place to the north of the city, it has a WIFI zone and a cycle route. It is host to many Micro-Soccer business championships. It is a good place to rest and enter the Historic Center of the city. It is located in the heart of one of the most traditional neighborhoods of the Vallenato cultural imaginary, from which it takes its name. Public space. Cortijos Park Recreation place that has tennis courts, beach volleyball, synthetic soccer, bio-healthy park, basketball courts and multifunctional. It also has wide green spaces to delight in cool shades. This sunny landscape that always bathes the city, attracts many visitors to the park all the time.Public space.
//fiestas Patronal Festival of La Candelaria This festival takes place during the month of February, in the municipality of Becerril.
Patronal of San Juan Bosco Celebration and veneration of the patron saint of the municipality of Bosconia, San Juan Bosco. January 31 begins with a musical dawn.
My Accordion Piece Festival It is celebrated in the municipality of El Paso. The organizing board of this festival created this event to pay tribute each year to the composer and musician that no one forgets: Alejandro Durán.
Valledupar livestock fair It is generally celebrated in the month of August. Cesar is considered an eminently agricultural and livestock region.
Vallenata Legend Festival The Vallenata Legend Festival is celebrated in the city of Valledupar generally during the month of April.
Arhuaca Coffee and Backpack Festival It is celebrated in the municipality of Pueblo Bello in the month of July.
